# AI/ML Features — Walkthrough & Testing Guide

## Architecture

```
┌─────────────────┐     HTTP/JSON      ┌──────────────────┐     HTTP/JSON     ┌─────────────────┐
│  Angular SPA    │ ──────────────────▶ │  NestJS Backend  │ ────────────────▶ │  Python Flask   │
│  (port 4200)    │                     │  (port 3000)     │                   │  ML Service     │
│                 │ ◀────────────────── │                  │ ◀──────────────── │  (port 5000)    │
└─────────────────┘    AI results       └──────────────────┘   ML predictions  └─────────────────┘
                                              │                                       │
                                              ▼                                       │
                                        ┌──────────┐                                  │
                                        │ MongoDB  │   NestJS fetches data,            │
                                        │ (scoped  │   sends to Python,               │
                                        │ by user) │   Python computes,               │
                                        └──────────┘   returns results                │
```

**Communication flow:**
1. Frontend calls NestJS endpoint (e.g. `GET /analytics/stockout-risks`)
2. NestJS fetches purchases + sales from MongoDB (scoped by `companyId` from JWT)
3. NestJS sends data as JSON POST to Python Flask (e.g. `POST http://localhost:5000/ml/stockout`)
4. Python runs ML algorithm, returns JSON result
5. NestJS returns result to frontend

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Python never accesses MongoDB directly. All data isolation is enforced by NestJS.

